gw.plugin.rateflow

Interface RateBookPreloadPlugin

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin, java.rmi.Remote

    public interface RateBookPreloadPlugin
extends com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin
    Plugin for controlling rate book preload and export to rate routines JAR.

    • Method Detail

      • getRateBooksToPreload

        java.lang.Iterable<RateBook> getRateBooksToPreload()
        Provides the list of rate books that should be preloaded,

        Recommended:

        1. Draft: Do not preload
        2. Stage: Do not preload
        3. Approved: Do not preload, unless you plan to make it Active right away
        4. Active:
          1. Not expired, and effective date in future: Preload.
          2. Not expired, and effective date in past: Preload "latest" of books with same Code
        Returns:
        list of rate books to preload
        See Also:
        RateBookStatus

      • getRateBooksToExportToJAR

        java.lang.Iterable<RateBook> getRateBooksToExportToJAR()
        Provides the list of rate books that should be exported to a JAR. The list of rate books returned must include all rate books that have rate routines that may be needed for rating, including re-rating previously rated policies. That is, if a rate routine is needed for rating then it is required that the rate routine belongs to at least one of the rate books returned.

        Only export Active rate books to the rate routines JAR

        Returns:
        list of rate books to be exported to a JAR

      • update

        void update(RateBookEvent event)
        Called to update the rate routines JAR when an event such as a rate book import or activation happens.

        Should be called after the event has occurred, i.e., changes have been written to the database. This may require calling this method from a bundle transaction callback's afterCommit() method.

        Parameters:
        event - a event relating to rate books that may cause the list of rate books to export to JAR to change
        See Also:
        BundleTransactionCallback
